MANDATORY ATTRIBUTION CONDITIONS

The following attribution conditions are NON-NEGOTIABLE and binding.
Violations constitute copyright infringement and immediate license termination.
These conditions apply regardless of:
  • Deployment environment (development, staging, production)
  • Hosting model (self-hosted, cloud, serverless, containerized)
  • Whether code is modified or unmodified
  • Whether the marketplace is public, private, or internal
  • Whether the marketplace is free or commercial

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 1 — API DOCUMENTATION ATTRIBUTION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

YOUR API DOCUMENTATION MUST include an "Attribution" or "Credits" section
that includes ALL of the following fields, exactly as written, in this order:

    Marketplace Backend powered by Himanshu's E-Commerce Framework
    Original author: Himanshu (https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu)
    Repository: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu/vridhira-backend
    License: E-Commerce Marketplace Attribution License v2.0

MANDATORY DOCUMENTATION PROPERTIES:
  ✓ Must appear in primary API documentation (README, API.md, Swagger docs)
  ✓ Visible on first load / above the fold
  ✓ Hyperlinks must be ACTIVE and working
  ✓ Applied with contrasting color (4.5:1 minimum contrast ratio)
  ✓ Font size minimum 11px
  ✓ All four fields present, unmodified, in exact order
  ✓ If API docs are auto-generated, attribution must be hardcoded in template

VIOLATIONS include:
  • Paraphrasing, summarizing, or abbreviating the attribution
  • Moving attribution to "hidden" documentation or changelogs
  • Replacing with vague language like "Based on an open-source project..."
  • Removing URLs or replacing with non-functional references
  • Burying attribution behind login walls or access restrictions
  • Claiming the API architecture as original work

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 2 — SOURCE CODE & CONFIGURATION ATTRIBUTION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ALL source code files (TypeScript, JavaScript, Python, Go, etc.) containing
Licensor code MUST retain the original copyright header. This includes:
  • API route handlers and controllers
  • Service layers and business logic
  • Database models and migrations
  • Authentication and authorization modules
  • Payment processing and order pipelines
  • Vendor management systems
  • Utility functions and helpers

REQUIRED HEADER PRESERVATION:
  (a) EXACT TEXT at top of file:
      /*
       * Copyright (c) 2026 Himanshu
       * Original source: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu/vridhira-backend
       * License: E-Commerce Marketplace Attribution License v2.0
       *
       * [Your additions here]
       */

  (b) You MAY:
      • Add your own copyright notices AFTER the original header
      • Add comments explaining your modifications
      • Refactor and optimize the code

  (c) You MAY NOT:
      • Remove or comment-out the original header
      • Modify the author name or repository reference
      • Move the header elsewhere in the file
      • Replace the header with your own copyright
      • Delete or rewrite this LICENSE file

(d) CONFIGURATION FILES also require headers:
     • .env files: Include comment with attribution
     • medusa-config.ts: Retain original config comments
     • Database migrations: Include header noting origin
     • Docker/K8s manifests: Include attribution in comments

Example .env attribution:
     # ====================================================
     # Based on Himanshu's E-Commerce Marketplace Framework
     # License: E-Commerce Marketplace Attribution License v2.0
     # ====================================================

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 3 — DEPLOYMENT & RUNTIME ATTRIBUTION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

When the Backend Software is deployed and operational, attribution MUST be
available in the following locations at all times:

  (a) API RESPONSE HEADERS:
      Every API endpoint response MUST include:
      X-Powered-By: Himanshu-Marketplace Framework v2.0
      X-License-Attribution: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu

  (b) ERROR RESPONSES:
      All error pages, error logs, and error messages MUST include:
      "System powered by Himanshu's E-Commerce Framework"
      This applies to:
      • 500 error pages (visible to admins)
      • Application logs (server/application logs)
      • Debug mode error outputs
      • Health check endpoints (must return attribution JSON)

      Example JSON response:
      {
        "error": "Internal Server Error",
        "framework": "Himanshu-Marketplace-Framework v2.0",
        "license": "https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu/vridhira-backend"
      }

  (c) ADMIN DASHBOARD:
      If you provide an admin interface:
      • Footer MUST contain: "Admin system built with Himanshu's framework"
      • System health/info page MUST list original framework
      • Accessible via admin menu → About/System Info

  (d) DATABASE/LOGS:
      • Initial migration logs MUST reference attribution
      • System startup logs MUST log: Initializing Marketplace Framework
        by Himanshu - License v2.0
      • README/changelog MUST document the original project

  (e) DEPLOYMENT ARTIFACTS:
      • Docker images: LABEL maintainer="Based on Himanshu's framework"
      • Kubernetes manifests: Include annotations
      • Serverless function environment: Set env vars with attribution
      • Container registries: Description must credit Himanshu

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 4 — ARCHITECTURAL COMPONENTS DOCUMENTATION
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you include, use, or significantly base your implementation on:
  • Order processing pipelines
  • Vendor management systems
  • Inventory tracking modules
  • Payment gateway integrations
  • Multi-tenant architecture
  • Product categorization systems
  • Review/rating systems
  • Admin role-based access control

You MUST document in ARCHITECTURE.md or COMPONENTS.md:
  • Original component name from this Software
  • Current implementation name
  • Modifications made (Y/N + brief description)
  • Link to original source in repository
  • Percentage of original code retained (est.)

PROHIBITED:
  • Obscuring the origin through complete rewrite
  • Claiming original architecture without acknowledging base
  • Removing all evidence of original component usage
  • Hiding implementation sources from team members

───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CONDITION 5 — VENDOR/PARTNER DISCLOSURE
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

If you are a vendor, partner, or agency deploying this Backend Software
for a client:

  (a) You MUST disclose to the client:
      • That the backend is based on Himanshu's framework
      • Link to: https://github.com/Newbie-Himanshu/vridhira-backend
      • This License's terms

  (b) Disclosure must be in:
      • Project proposal/contract (technology section)
      • Technical documentation delivered to client
      • System architecture documentation

  (c) You may NOT:
      • Represent the Software as your own original work
      • Hide the framework's origin from the client
      • Claim exclusive rights to the code
      • Prevent the client from knowing the true origin

