BREACH DETECTION & VERIFICATION

The Licensor may enforce compliance through:

  1. AUTOMATED MONITORING:
     • Crawling API endpoints and checking response headers
     • Scanning GitHub/GitLab public repositories
     • DNS/web scraping of publicly deployed instances
     • Log file analysis for attribution mentions

  2. DIRECT VERIFICATION:
     • Accessing admin endpoints to verify attribution
     • Requesting access to source code for audit
     • Testing API error responses for proper attribution
     • Reviewing deployment configurations

  3. ESCALATION PROCESS:
     • Initial breach notice (email, issue, PR)
     • 3 business days to respond/acknowledge
     • 7 calendar days to remediate (first violation)
     • 3 calendar days to remediate (subsequent violations)
     • Permanent termination on third+ violation

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

TERMINATION AND ENFORCEMENT

1. AUTOMATIC TERMINATION
   Any violation immediately and automatically terminates all rights.
   Upon termination you must:
     • Cease all use within 24 hours
     • Take all deployments offline within 48 hours
     • Notify Licensor of compliance
     • Provide proof of data migration to alternative system
     • Provide proof of Software deletion

2. CURE PERIOD
   • Pre-production violations: 14 days to cure, unlimited reinstatements
   • Production violations (first): 7 days to cure
   • Production violations (second+): 3 days, then permanent termination
   • Intentional violations (deliberate removal): NO cure period

3. DAMAGES FOR BREACH
   You agree that damages are impossible to calculate accurately, and agree
   to pay liquidated damages upon demand:
     • $1,000 USD per day of production violation
     • $5,000 USD per instance of header removal
     • $10,000 USD per hidden attribution instance
     • $50,000 USD for vendor misrepresentation to client
     • All legal fees, court costs, and enforcement expenses
     • Injunctive relief to remove from production

4. MONITORING AUTHORIZATION
   You authorize the Licensor to:
     • Access deployed APIs to verify attribution compliance
     • Crawl public instances to check for violations
     • Request access to staging/production environments for audits
     • Scan repositories irregularly for compliance checks

5. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION
   This License is governed by the laws of India. You:
     • Consent to exclusive jurisdiction of Indian courts
     • Waive objections to enforcement in Indian courts
     • Agree to bear all costs of international enforcement
     • Acknowledge Indian Copyright Act, 1957 penalties apply

